            <article>
                <h2>Facts about ottoman empire</h2>
                <p>The Ottoman Empire, a vast and enduring empire spanning across Asia, Europe, and Africa, originated in the late 13th
                century and lasted until 1922. Founded by Osman I, it emerged from a small Turkish principality in Anatolia, eventually
                expanding its influence through military prowess and strategic conquests. At its height, the empire encompassed
                territories in the Balkans, the Middle East, and North Africa, with Constantinople (Istanbul) as its capital. The empire
                is notable for its longevity, its multi-ethnic and multi-religious character, and its role in shaping the political landscape of the mediterranean and beyond.</p>
            </article>
           
            <aside>
                <h3>Ottoman Empire</h3>
              
                <p>The Ottoman Empire, a vast and enduring empire spanning across Asia, Europe, and Africa, originated in the late 13th
                century and lasted until 1922. Founded by Osman I, it emerged from a small Turkish principality in Anatolia, eventually
                expanding its influence through military prowess and strategic conquests. At its height, the empire encompassed
                territories in the Balkans, the Middle East, and North Africa, with Constantinople (Istanbul) as its capital. The empire
                is notable for its longevity, its multi-ethnic and multi-religious character, and its role in shaping the political landscape of the mediterranean and beyond.</p></aside></section>
